_Language" title="Dictionary of the Scots Language">Dictionary of the Scots Language</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Doric_dialect_(Scotland)" title="Doric dialect (Scotland)">Doric dialect (Scotland)</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Glasgow_patter" title="Glasgow patter">Glasgow patter</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Billy_Kay_(writer)" title="Billy Kay (writer)">Billy Kay</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Lallans" title="Lallans">Lallans</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Languages_of_the_United_Kingdom" title="Languages of the United Kingdom">Languages of the United Kingdom</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Modern_Scots" title="Modern Scots">Modern Scots</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Phonological_history_of_Scots" title="Phonological history of Scots">Phonological history of Scots</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Scotticism" title="Scotticism">Scotticism</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Scottish_Corpus_of_Texts_and_Speech" title="Scottish Corpus of Texts and Speech">Scottish Corpus of Texts and Speech</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Scottish_English" title="Scottish English">Scottish English</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Scottish_literature" title="Scottish literature">Scottish literature</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Ulster_Scots_dialects" title="Ulster Scots dialects">Ulster-Scots (Ullans)</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Scots_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: References">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist columns references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">7% of the population (100,000\xe2\x80\x93115,000) report using Scots at home in the 2